    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Engineers are tech specialists and the only ones able to employ their powerful combat drones onto the battlefield to do their bidding.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hit Die:&nbsp;</strong>d8</li>\n<li><strong>Primary Ability:&nbsp;</strong>Intelligence</li>\n<li><strong>Saves:&nbsp;</strong>Constitution &amp; Intelligence</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"enfilade\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Enfilade</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Starting at 2nd level, if an ally uses a power that primes an enemy within 10m, you may use your reaction to detonate the primed enemy with a quick tech burst that cannot miss.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p>\n<h4 id=\"jack-of-all-trades\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Jack of All Trades</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Starting at 2nd level, you can add half your proficiency bonus, rounded down, to any ability check you make that doesn't already include your proficiency bonus.</p>\n<h4 id=\"extra-attack\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Extra Attack</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Beginning at 6th level, you can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.</p>\n<h4 id=\"disrupting-attack\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Disrupting Attack</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">At 10th level, you learn how to make your weapon strikes undercut a creature's resistance to your tech spells. When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, that creature has disadvantage on the next saving throw it makes against a spell you cast before the end of your next turn.</p>\n<h4 id=\"tactical-advantage\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Tactical Advantage</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Starting at 14th level, when you prepare an advanced version of a spell you prepare both advancements. When you cast an advanced spell you can choose to cast either advancement option.</p>\n<h4 id=\"spell-steal\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Spell Steal</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">At 18th level, you gain the ability to clone spell effects onto your omni-tool.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Immediately after a creature casts a spell that targets you or includes you in its area of effect, you can use your reaction to force the creature to make a saving throw with its spellcasting ability modifier. The DC equals your spell save DC. On a failed save, you negate the spell's effect on you and you copy a temporary version of the spell onto your omni-tool if it is at least 1st level and of a level you can cast (it does not have to be a tech spell). For the next 8 hours, you know the spell and can cast it using your tech points. The creature can't cast that spell until the 8 hours have passed.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.</p>",
